        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 5:22PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a slow-moving thunderstorm
near Douds, or 9 miles south of Fairfield, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Strong winds could break tree limbs, knock down weak trees
and blow around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairfield, Batavia, Birmingham, Libertyville, Maharishi Vedic City,
Douds, Jefferson County Park, Brookville, Fairfield Municipal
Airport, Collett, Selma, and Jefferson County Fairgrounds.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
